The paper discusses beamforming structures for cellular multiuser MIMO systems with a large number of antennas, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The focus on energy efficiency and hardware complexity also suggests a possible fit for systems and control (cs.SY). The use of millimeter waves and antenna arrays suggests a possible fit for multimedia (cs.MM) and architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories.
